//If you experience grid pattern when using LoRA on the second pass upscaling

Most high-rank LoRA models tend to produce grid pattern artifacts when rendered at high resolutions (outside the optimal flux range). 

These artifacts become even more noticeable with higher denoise values, especially during the second-pass upscaling, as seen here with the ControlNet sampler (which has a hardcoded denoise value of 1).

To remove these artifacts, use this node to lower the values of the first three "double blocks" in your LoRA stack.
